/////////////////////////////////////////////
// Externe und Interne Benutzer
//////////////////////////////
// Internal Testers
//////////////////////
// Each app can be tested by up to 25 members of your team who have been assigned the Admin, App Manager,
// Developer, or Marketer role in iTunes Connect. Each member can test on up to 30 devices.
// Internal testers can access all of your beta builds available for testing.
//////////////////////
// External testers
////////////////////
// + Once youâ€™re ready, you can invite up to 10,000 external testers who do not need to be part of
//   your team to beta test an app that you intend for public release on the App Store.
// + You can organize external testers into custom groups and share different builds with each group,
//   depending on which features you want them to test.
// + Before external testing can begin, the app must pass Beta App Review to make sure it complies with
//   the full App Store Review Guidelines. Only the first build for the beta version requires a full review.
/////////////////////////////
// Einladung erneut senden
// + http://de.iosberry.com/so-senden-sie-externe-testereinladungen-erneut-an-apples-testflight-dienst.html

//////////////////////////////////
// Summarized
////////////////
// + Maximum 25 internal Testers
// + Maximim of 10000 external testers per App
// + Builds are available for 90 days.
// + You can upload a new build to continue Testing
// + You can turn off testing at any time.
// + iOS 8 or higher.

///////////////////////////////
// Multiple Builds of one App
/////////////////////////////
// If a tester is assigned to multiple groups and Builds
// Testflight always shows the latest build version for
// installation and download.

//////////////////////////////////
// Using Testflight Step-by-Step
////////////////////////////////
// 1. Open App and TestFlight
// 2. Fill in the Testinformation
// 3. Add iTunes Connect Users. (INTERNAL Testers)
//    .. Adding testers of my team.
//    .. Once a build is uploaded all internal testers are automatically notfified.

///////////////////////////////////
// Adding External Testers
// 1. Add External testers, which are not part of my Team
//    .. Add a group. The group name can be edited later.
// 2. Add new or existing Testers, Manually or by CSV
//    .. Email is mandatory. First and last names are optional
// 3. Add a build to the group.
//    .. Click on Builds
//    .. Select the build you want to add.
// 4. Add Testing information.
//    .. Testing information can be localized.
// 5. Submit for review.
////////////////////////////////////////////
// + You can add more testers and start testing once the build is approved.
// + You can add more builds to a group
// + You can add more groups and send builds to them as well.

///////////////////////////////
// All Testers
///////////////////////////////
// + Shows all engaged testers
